Dear Team,



Greetings from Health Wealth Management.



We are into corporate wellness, providing comprehensive healthcare solutions, including preventive health camps, diagnostic coordination, employee wellness management, and end-to-end medical support services for companies and institutions across India.



As part of our digital expansion, we are enhancing our website to deliver a seamless and integrated healthcare experience to our users. To support this initiative, we are exploring a partnership for API integration with your pharmacy services.



This integration would enable our platform to offer:

Medicine catalogue access

Real-time availability checks

Order placement and tracking

Prescription upload and fulfilment




We believe this collaboration will greatly enhance the user experience on our portal while driving additional order flow and visibility to your pharmacy.



Health Wealth Management is fully committed to complying with all regulatory and operational guidelines related to pharmaceutical services and healthcare data management.



Kindly let us know a suitable time to connect and discuss this further. We look forward to the opportunity to collaborate.

Dear Team,

Greetings from Health Wealth Management.

We are into corporate wellness, providing comprehensive healthcare solutions, including preventive health camps, diagnostic coordination, employee wellness management, and end-to-end medical support services for companies and institutions across India.

As part of our digital expansion, we are enhancing our website to deliver a seamless and integrated healthcare experience to our users. To support this initiative, we are exploring a partnership for API integration with your pharmacy services.

This integration would enable our platform to offer:
  • Medicine catalogue access
  • Real-time availability checks
  • Order placement and tracking
  • Prescription upload and fulfilment

We believe this collaboration will greatly enhance the user experience on our portal while driving additional order flow and visibility to your pharmacy.

Health Wealth Management is fully committed to complying with all regulatory and operational guidelines related to pharmaceutical services and healthcare data management.

Kindly let us know a suitable time to connect and discuss this further. We look forward to the opportunity to collaborate.

Dear Sir/ Madam,

I had placed an order for medicines on 30 November, for which I had made
the payment while placing the order. On the same day, a packet was
delivered at 4.02pm, which was wrongly delivered to me, as the packet was
meant for someone else. The delivery person insisted that the payment for
that packet needs to be done. Hence, I made a UPI payment of Rs. 1159.17 on
November 30, at. 4.02pm, and the payment was made to Pharmeasy UPI id. I am
attaching a screenshot of the same.

My packets were delivered on 30 November evening and 3 December morning.
The latest packet was delivered by Mr. Bhupesh. The wrong packet I had
received on 30 November was handed over to Mr. Bhupesh to be delivered to
the correct recipient.

However, since I had made an excess payment of Rs. 1159.17 on 30 November
for this wrong packet, I request you to refund this amount.

Looking forward to your prompt action.

Regards,
Pranay Dandekar

helpdesk_ticket.description_html:
Dear Sir/ Madam,

I had placed an order for medicines on 30 November, for which I had made the payment while placing the order. On the same day, a packet was delivered at 4.02pm, which was wrongly delivered to me, as the packet was meant for someone else. The delivery person insisted that the payment for that packet needs to be done. Hence, I made a UPI payment of Rs. 1159.17 on November 30, at. 4.02pm, and the payment was made to Pharmeasy UPI id. I am attaching a screenshot of the same.

My packets were delivered on 30 November evening and 3 December morning. The latest packet was delivered by Mr. Bhupesh. The wrong packet I had received on 30 November was handed over to Mr. Bhupesh to be delivered to the correct recipient. 

However, since I had made an excess payment of Rs. 1159.17 on 30 November for this wrong packet, I request you to refund this amount.

Looking forward to your prompt action.

Regards,
Pranay Dandekar
Mob: 9820668584

notes.body: Order ID: 653985033982844928-73729  The rider mistakenly delivered Customer A’s order to Customer B, and Customer B’s order was delivered to Customer A.  Customer B complained about receiving the wrong order and raised a pickup request. The pickup was completed successfully, and the refund was issued to Customer B. Later, the rider also delivered Customer B’s correct order.  Now, Customer A did not receive the correct order. That order has returned to the warehouse. Customer A has raised a complaint stating that the order was not received.  Example for clarity: Customer A’s order was delivered to Customer B, and Customer B’s order was delivered to Customer A. Customer B raised a pickup request for the wrong order, the pickup was completed, and the refund was issued. After that, Customer B received the correct order. Since the pickup and refund for Customer B have already been completed, the order cannot be returned to Customer A.  Please guide us on the next steps for this case
notes.body_html:
Order ID: 653985033982844928-73729

The rider mistakenly delivered Customer A’s order to Customer B, and Customer B’s order was delivered to Customer A.

Customer B complained about receiving the wrong order and raised a pickup request. The pickup was completed successfully, and the refund was issued to Customer B. Later, the rider also delivered Customer B’s correct order.

Now, Customer A did not receive the correct order. That order has returned to the warehouse. Customer A has raised a complaint stating that the order was not received.

Example for clarity:
Customer A’s order was delivered to Customer B, and Customer B’s order was delivered to Customer A.
Customer B raised a pickup request for the wrong order, the pickup was completed, and the refund was issued. After that, Customer B received the correct order.
Since the pickup and refund for Customer B have already been completed, the order cannot be returned to Customer A.

Please guide us on the next steps for this case

notes.body: Hello Shubhangi,      Greetings from PharmEasy!       I am sorry to know that you are unable to operate the PharmEasy application. We aim to provide the best service, however, situations like these are rare.      Please be informed that at times, due to network issues, you may face such technical issues. As a quick fix, I request you to clear your browsing cookies and cache and reinstall your PharmEasy application and connect to a stable network.
